    (10, 0, 'Ambiguous', 'Objection, ambiguous. Cal. Judges Benchbook Civ. Proc. Discovery (August 2019), § 18.35.', 'Objection, ambiguous. Cal. Judges Benchbook Civ. Proc. Discovery (August 2019), § 18.35.\r\n\r\n<b>Use Notes</b>\r\nThis is only a valid objection if interrogatory is wholly unintelligible. An interrogatory must be answered if &quot;the nature of the information sought is apparent.&quot; <i>Deyo v Kilbourne</i> (1978) 84 CA3d 771, 783.', 1,1,1,0,0),
